   },
   "source": [
    "# Planetary Motion"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-05T13:35:06.900890Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-05T13:35:06.100022Z"
    },
    "jupyter": {
     "outputs_hidden": false
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "skip"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from scipy.integrate import odeint\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib import animation\n",
    "\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "%config InlineBackend.figure_format = 'retina'\n",
    "\n",
    "# default values for plotting\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 12,\n",
    "                     'axes.titlesize': 18,\n",
    "                     'axes.labelsize': 16,\n",
    "                     'axes.labelpad': 14,\n",
    "                     'lines.linewidth': 1,\n",
    "                     'lines.markersize': 10,\n",
    "                     'xtick.labelsize' : 16,\n",
    "                     'ytick.labelsize' : 16,\n",
    "                     'xtick.top' : True,\n",
    "                     'xtick.direction' : 'in',\n",
    "                     'ytick.right' : True,\n",
    "                     'ytick.direction' : 'in',}) \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Physical Model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "From the above defined equation of motion for the spring pendulum, it is only a small step to simulate planetary motion, which you should know well from you mechanics lectures. The equations of motion in angular and radial direction can be obtained very similarly. Here, however, there is no force in the tangential direction as we deal with the central symmetric gravitational potential. The equations of motion read:\n",
    "\n",
    "\\begin{eqnarray}\n",
    "\\ddot{r}&=&r\\dot{\\theta}^2-\\frac{G\\, M}{r^2}\\\\\n",
    "\\ddot{\\theta}&=&-\\frac{1}{r}2\\dot{r}\\dot{\\theta}\n",
    "\\end{eqnarray}\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "We know the resulting trajectory of this motion \n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "r(\\theta)=\\frac{p}{1+\\epsilon \\cos(\\theta)}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "with\n",
    "\n",
    "\\begin{equation}\n",
    "p=\\frac{L^2}{G M m^2}\n",
    "\\end{equation}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\\begin{equation}\n",
    "\\epsilon=\\sqrt{1+\\frac{2\\frac{E}{m}\\frac{L^2}{m^2}}{G^2M^2}}\n",
    "\\end{equation}\n",
    "\n",
    "The trajectory is therefore determined by $p$ and the excentricity $\\epsilon$. For $0<\\epsilon<1$(E<0) there is a closed orbit with an ellipctical shape. For $\\epsilon=0$ the orbit is circular."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-05T13:37:06.853562Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-05T13:37:06.850859Z"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def planetary_motion(state, time ): \n",
    "    g0 = state[1]\n",
    "    g1 = state[0]*state[3]**2 - G*M/(state[0]**2) \n",
    "    g2 = state[3]\n",
    "    g3 = -2.0*state[1]*state[3]/state[0]\n",
    "    return np.array([g0, g1, g2, g3]) "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Numerical Solution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Initial Parameters: Planets"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:34.184602Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:34.180401Z"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# mass m1, m2, length of pendula L1, L2, position of the coupling, spring constant k, gravitational acceleration\n",
    "G=4*np.pi**2\n",
    "M=1 # mass of the sun\n",
    "m=1 # mass of the earth\n",
    "\n",
    "N = 10000\n",
    "state = np.zeros ([4])\n",
    "r_o= 1.8 # initial radius\n",
    "v_o = 0 # initial radial velocity\n",
    "theta_o = 0 # initial angle\n",
    "omega_o = 1# initial angular velocity, for 2.222 it becomes circular\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "state[0]=r_o\n",
    "state[1]=v_o \n",
    "state[2] = theta_o \n",
    "state[3] = omega_o\n",
    "\n",
    "time = np.linspace(0, 3, N)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-05T09:32:41.773398Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-05T09:32:41.770960Z"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Solution: Planets"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:35.196330Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:35.186063Z"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "answer = odeint ( planetary_motion , state , time )\n",
    "\n",
    "xdata = answer[:,0]*np.cos(answer[:,2])\n",
    "ydata = answer[:,0]*np.sin(answer[:,2]) "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:35.702508Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:35.699702Z"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ellipse parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "L=m*r_o**2*omega_o # angular momentum\n",
    "E=0.5*m*(v_o**2+r_o**2*omega_o**2)-G*M*m/r_o\n",
    "\n",
    "p=(L/m)**2/(G*M)\n",
    "e=np.sqrt(1+(2*E*L**2/(m**3))/(G*G*M*M))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Plotting: Planets"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-05T09:33:11.142411Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-05T09:33:11.139501Z"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Trajectory"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:38.160999Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:37.993756Z"
    },
    "jupyter": {
     "outputs_hidden": false
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 700x700 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 593,
       "width": 639
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# analytical solution\n",
    "theta=np.linspace(0,2*np.pi,1000)\n",
    "r=p/(1+e*np.cos(theta))\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "fig=plt.figure(1, figsize = (7,7) )\n",
    "plt.plot(xdata,ydata,'k-',lw=5,alpha=0.3,label='numerical')\n",
    "plt.plot(-r*np.cos(theta),r*np.sin(theta),'k--',lw=1,label='analytical')\n",
    "plt.plot(0,0,'o')\n",
    "plt.xlim(-2,2)\n",
    "plt.ylim(-2,2)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Energy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:41.622212Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:41.618250Z"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Etot=0.5*m*(answer[:,1]**2+answer[:,0]**2*answer[:,3]**2)-G*M*m/answer[:,0]\n",
    "Ekin=0.5*m*(answer[:,1]**2+answer[:,0]**2*answer[:,3]**2)\n",
    "Epot=-G*M*m/answer[:,0]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:42.918865Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-05T13:38:42.782875Z"
    },
    "jupyter": {
     "outputs_hidden": false
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 465,
       "width": 622
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.plot(time,Ekin,label=\"E_kin\")\n",
    "plt.plot(time,Epot,label=\"E_pot\")\n",
    "plt.plot(time,Etot)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('time')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('energy')\n",
    "plt.ylim(-100,100)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
